column13: An improved method of lubrication of a controlledslip differential comprises using a lubricant comprising a static friction reducing amount of an aliphatic phosphate ester and a hydrocarbon base stock having a kinematic viscosity at 210 DEG F. in the range of 1.5-200.0 c.s. and containing a major amount of a hydrogenated polymer of C3-C12 olefin, such as a "true" isobutylene oligomer or of a blend of at least one C13-C29 naphthene and from 0.1-20 parts by weight, based on said naphthene of at least one member from at least one of the following groups (a), (b), (c) and (d):
